description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric Speech and Language Therapist Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic speech and language therapist to join our established team in East Cheshire. The post holder will deliver a service to children and young people with a range of speech, language and communication needs around our borough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work with children in a variety of settings such as community clinics, nurseries and home visits. They will work closely with parents, teaching staff and other health professionals to provide a coordinated service to the children and young people in all settings. The post holder will have experience of carrying out formal and informal assessments and a sound knowledge of evidence based interventions for a range of clinical presentations such as speech sound delays/disorders and DLD. They will also have knowledge and experience of setting SMART targets and modelling strategies and explaining advice to parents and other professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be an integral part of a supportive and innovative team where training and personal development is actively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 22.5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced with Barred list Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Careers website with lots of information on how to join our team and Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Jennifer Heywood Job title Speech and Language Therapy Team Manager Email address jenniferheywood@nhs.net Telephone number 01625 661881&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liz Dunne and Jennifer Heywood&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paediatric Speech and Language Therapy Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
